rComments: Honestly, he's simply a sweetheart. He is very understanding and reasonable. Midterm and final were super straight forward, no need to stress about studying. That being said, the topics covered in EESA01 are mostly common sense and easy to understand so I can't comment on his actual teaching abilities.

Dr. Martin always brightened my day in class. He cares allot about his students and wants them to do well. Dr. Martin knows the course content very well, it was always fun to attend his lectures. He is also very accessible outside class and i enjoyed the course.

I just wanna say this was my first course with prof martin and he turned out to be the best prof ever , he literally explains everything and also made both the midterm and the final an easy A , he will literally tell u what part of a topic he is gonna test us on which made my life a whole lot easier while studying for this course .

Professor Martin is the best prof ever. He tells you exactly what you need to study for the midterm and final by creating study guides which are super helpful. If you study from the study guide, you are guaranteed to do well. He also explains content really well and he is always happy to answer questions or clarify material. Best prof ever!

Honestly he made my first sem in uni amazing. He was an amazing prof, really taught well to ensure everyone understood everything clearly. He gives you a mark breakdown for the midterm and final! His exam and midterm were fair, as in if you studied, you're bless. 10/10 HE IS AMAZING

Adam Martin is the best prof at UTSC, nice, super helpful. And honestly, such a wonderful professor to be taught by. You can always get the support from him, and explain everything to you grading etc. clear, never make student's life difficult. He's leaving at the end of this semester, feel a little bit sad honestly.
Adam Martin is a very understanding teacher. He is GREAT!
BEST PROF AT UTSC. wish others could learn from him. Doesn't like to make students' lives difficult by making them study unnecessary things.

such a nice prof, always brightens up my day and my mood if it is bad. He makes soil interesting and gets his students engaged. theres something about the way he teaches that makes me want to listen to him. I like that he doesn't use big words to describe other big words he genuinely teaches the material properly

Adam is a great prof. His exams are straightforward because he essentially tells you what is important and what is not by making study guide slides which is all you need for studying. Having said that, it is necessary to attend lecture as this is where he gives you the hints. They usually end early anyway. 10/10

Very caring and nicest prof so far in uoft for sure! He loves talking to his students and get to know them. Everything based on lecture, no book needed. Exams are TOUGH, get ready to memorize each slide! i worked like a dog and got an A+ but i know ppl who got 60s b/c they thought the course was gona be easy cuz he is soo nice.
Honestly, such a wonderful professor to be taught by.

This is my favorite prof in the whole university! He is very kind and caring and takes time to personally go up and speak to his student before class. His lecture voice is very calm and helps me pay attention to what he is saying. He also provides detailed answers on the important things that we need to study.
Best Prof UTSC has to offer, a very inspirational and hard working prof!

Prof Martin has been the best prof I've had at University of Toronto. He's very easy to approach and engages with his students. If you have any questions he will do his very best to answer them to the best of his ability. For the amount of material he could have tested on, he was very fair with the amount actually on the midterm & final.
Definitely the best Prof I have in University of Toronto. Cares for his students and clear in his lectures. However, he has extremely long lecture slides (100+ slides)
Best prof ever. His lectures are amazing, and he makes everything very understandable.

Somehow, he was able to make a course about soil really interesting. Took the time to explain concepts I didn't understand thoroughly in office hours. Overall a nice person and great prof. Labs and tests are fair. 10/10 would recommend.
